field.value:
Quoting from forum post:

Add the mapping information auto-import="false" to the nhibernate node. You can do this, when you change the StartMappingNode() method in XmlGenerationVisitor class like that:
Code:
private void StartMappingNode()
      {
         Append( "<hibernate-mapping auto-import=\"false\" xmlns:xsd=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema\" " +
            "xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xmlns=\"urn:nhibernate-mapping-2.0\">" );
      }

Additionally you must change method calls like Type.Name in ActiveRecordBase class to Type.FullName. Now some tests failed because the length of the mapping-information changed, so you must add auto-import=\"false\" to every mapping comparison test. Be aware that now you must use the full class name in queries.
